d the house. He wrote affectionately, dreamily, recalling the wet catkins on the slippery footbridge of the pavilion where they first met.

In those days letters took a long time on the way—the answer did not come until July.

“Thank you very much for your good, sweet, ‘southern’ letter. Why do you write that you still remember me? And you’ll not forget me? No? How lovely!

“Today it’s so nice and fresh, after a thunderstorm. As at Voskresensk—remember? Wouldn’t you like to wan